The Mahomet Aquifer in central IL is a sole source aquifer and is the only source of drinking water for more than 500,000 people in 15 counties

Illinois worked hard to get the Mahomet Aquifer designated a sole source Aquifer. That should mean additional protection. But the responsible agencies are NOT protecting it.

Fanter Farms recently applied for a Beginner Farmer Loan through the USDA direct and guaranteed Farm Service Agency (FSA) loan program to construct a 2,400 head swine CAFO. FSA must consider the potential impact on local water sources and ecology with an environmental review.

Talking to Karen Hudson, co-founder of Illinois Coalition for Clean Air and Water (ICCAW), Chris Petersen, independent regenerative/sustainable family farmer and a member of Socially Responsible Agriculture Project and Kathy Martin, an engineer and technical assistant to SRAP.

So why is a hog CAFO being considered over Mahomet Aquifer in Mason County? This CAFO would arise between the towns of Havana and Kilbourne. Fanter Farms recently applied for a Beginner Farmer Loan through the USDA direct and guaranteed Farm Service Agency (FSA) loan program.

EPA can designate  an aquifer as a “sole source” if contamination of the aquifer would create a significant hazard to public health, with no physically available or economically feasible alternative sources of drinking water to serve the population that relies on the aquifer.

What would you do if a 2,480 head hog CAFO set up shop across the street from your home? You would inhale hydrogen sulfide, ammonia, endotoxins, volatile organic compounds, disinfectants, dried fecal matter and more. And that's just the beginning.

Contemplating several experiences from the past; You have no control over what people think or say about you, it’s their narrative. All you can do is live authentically. People wise enough to see will recognize the truth, those who don’t…again, you have no control over that.

3/3  Creativity doesn’t have to be big. Sing a simple song, change one ingredient in a recipe, learn a new dance step, adjust your space. Don’t worry if it’s not perfect. It’s not a competition, just have fun with it. Shine your brilliant light! #Creative #shineyourlight

2/3  Who told you you’re not creative? They were wrong. Realize that you exist because your ancestors constantly figured out innovations; new ways to survive in times of change, making do with what was available, creativity is your birthright. #creativity #innovation

1/3   Let your inner light shine! All humans are innately creative, you don’t have to be an artist, writer, musician, or poet to be creative. Any challenge in life is an opportunity to innovate, create, and design the life you want to live. #create #shine
